main event: Three unidentified objects were sighted flying over Oak Ridge, Tennessee at an estimated altitude of 1000 ft on 19 June 1949 for about 12-15 minutes.
interesting points: The objects were described as consisting of two identical rectangular-shaped objects coordinated in movement, and a third circular-shaped object in level flight above the two rectangular objects.
The rectangular objects appeared to be bright metal on top, dark underneath, while the circular object was the color of frosted glass.
No noise was heard to indicate how the objects were being propelled, and they did not appear to gain or lose altitude while in view.
The weather was clear with high cumulus clouds, and a slight easterly wind.
The witnesses of the objects were described as reputable people, including a biologist, a school teacher, and the wife of a member of the Security Division, AEC, Oak Ridge, Tennessee.
